commit.message:
Revert quantizations that yielded larger pngs

Turns out it's better to check than to assume. 41 of the 197 icons
actually grew (slightly) larger from the previous changes.

Optimize brush previews further using indexing

The pngnq quantizer is applied to most preview icons, except for
those where visible banding appears even at a table size of 256.

Reduces size by another 600K, at no real perceivable loss in quality
(verified by creating montages w. feh, and diffing them with
imagemagick; there is some loss of detail, but it's very subtle).

Merge pull request #3 from Rigo-V/master

commit.message:
autogen: simplify the whole automake version check.

I don't think we need this long version casing (I hope I am not just
getting rid of years of wisdom in a whim! ;p). Let's make it simple and
test whatever is the default version on the build system.

Well I could see this breaking if the default automake is older than the
minimum requirement, yet another acceptable version was installed. But
seeing how old is our requirement, I doubt it would happen (I hope!).

Replace hardcoded aclocal / automake versions

The required version check will be done anyway, so there is no need to require a specific binary.

Adding autotools installation.

So I realize that scons installation is broken with Scons 3!
Scons 3 now uses Python 3 and there seems to be no way out of it (that I
could find by searching the web and reading scons manual, at least).
Scons 3 has only been out for a few months (September 2017) but some
distributions (like Fedora) already started to replace and ship these
new versions. In such a situation, the real fix would be to update
SCons* files so that they use Python code compatible both with Python 2
and 3, and then later maintenance must always take care it works with
both version at each update. That is just too cumbersome and just making
an autotools build was so much more easier and faster.

I leave the old SCons* files for the time being because they still work
with older scons 2.x version, but that will probably have to be removed
at some point, especially when all distributions out there will stop
shipping scons 2.x.

Cherry picked from commit bfe0c987370b9925bd91fd6da2da3f6ecba5f809, with
configure.ac updated to install version 2.0.
